I had time to return to my car on the opposite side for my binoculars; it was early evening  so I couldn't see the adult bird clearly with a naked eye. The adult munia was perched within a tall shrub, but it wasn't moving or vocalizing. Then I saw the juvenile approach the adult before they both flew off. The begging call went on for 10-15 minutes while I was there. Other background sounds include passersby.
